nded manual follow-up:\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Inspect the run logs to identify the first Gradle or agent failure.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Review the preserved branch and decide which generated changes can be salvaged.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Re-run the workflow or continue manually after addressing the root cause.\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n\\ndef claimed_issue_worktree_is_valid(claimed_issue: ClaimedIssue, stage: str) -> bool:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return True when analysis agents may safely run in the claimed issue worktree.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    try:\\n        require_claimed_issue_worktree(claimed_issue, stage)\\n        return True\\n    except Exception as exc:\\n        print(\\n            (\\n                f\\\"ERROR: Skipping {stage} for issue #{claimed_issue.issue['number']} \\\"\\n                f\\\"because the claimed worktree is invalid: {exc!r}\\\"\\n            ),\\n            file=sys.stderr,\\n        )\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n87:{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_46\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '2688,2735p' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/forge_metadata.py\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n88:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_46\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '2688,2735p' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/forge_metadata.py\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"        f\\\"- Library: {claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}\\\\n\\\"\\n        f\\\"- Workflow strategy: {candidate.strategy_name}\\\\n\\\"\\n        f\\\"- Workflow status: {candidate.workflow_status}\\\\n\\\"\\n        f\\\"- Dynamic access coverage: {coverage.covered_calls}/{coverage.total_calls} \\\"\\n        f\\\"({coverage_percent:.2f}%) from {coverage.source}\\\\n\\\"\\n        f\\\"- Dynamic access report path: {report_path_display}\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"Task:\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \\\"\\n        \\\"Write the exact GitHub issue comment that should be posted because this library likely needs human follow-up.\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"Comment requirements:\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Start with a short heading: `Human intervention needed`.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Ground the explanation in concrete project observations.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- End with 2 or 3 specific manual next steps.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Keep the comment concise and do not use code fences.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Do not mention being an AI.\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n\\ndef _build_human_intervention_fallback_comment(\\n        claimed_issue: ClaimedIssue,\\n        candidate: HumanInterventionCandidate,\\n) -> str:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Build a deterministic fallback comment when the analysis agent fails.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if candidate.reason == \\\"test_generation_failed\\\" or candidate.coverage is None:\\n        return _build_failed_generation_fallback_comment(claimed_issue, candidate, [])\\n\\n    coverage_percent = candidate.coverage.coverage_ratio * 100.0\\n    return (\\n        \\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        f\\\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \\\"\\n        f\\\"`{candidate.coverage.covered_calls}/{candidate.coverage.total_calls}` ({coverage_percent:.2f}%). \\\"\\n        \\\"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"Recommended manual follow-up:\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Verify whether the library requires environment setup, fixtures, or execution paths that automation did not trigger.\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"- Add or adjust focused tests for the uncovered paths before relying on the generated metadata.\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n\\ndef _sanitize_log_name(value: str) -> str:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a filesystem-safe log name segment.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return re.sub(r\\\"[^A-Za-z0-9_.-]+\\\", \\\"_\\\", value).strip(\\\"_\\\") or \\\"unknown\\\"\\n\\n\\ndef _repo_relative_path(path: str, repo_path: str) -> str:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a path relative to the given repository root.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return os.path.relpath(os.path.abspath(path), os.path.abspath(repo_path))\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n89:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_47\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.springframework:spring-expression:6.2.8`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7502-fails-javac-compile-org.springframework-spring-expression-6.2.8-ff404e13\\n\\nThe original library-specific failure was `compileTestJava`: `ReflectivePropertyAccessorInnerOptimalPropertyAccessorTest.java` referenced `ReflectivePropertyAccessor.OptimalPropertyAccessor`, which is private in Spring Expression `6.2.8` (see line 27 and line 46 in `forge/logs/org.springframework:spring-expression:6.2.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-21T14-31-19-178307Z.log`, also captured in `forge/logs/org.springframework:spring-expression:6.2.8/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-21T14-31-49-320707Z.log`).\\n\\nThe preserved work appears to fix that javac issue. Later validation logs are successful: `forge/logs/org.springframework:spring-expression:6.2.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-21T14-39-10-125926Z.log`, `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-21T14-42-46-619114Z.log`, `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-21T14-42-47-076016Z.log`, and `logs/checkstyle/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-21T14-43-17-004957Z.log`. The run metrics in `stats/org.springframework/spring-expression/6.2.8/execution-metrics.json` also show strategy `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5` completed successfully in 3 iterations.\\n\\nThe most likely stage that still caused the workflow to end in `failure` is `native-test-verify` during `generateMetadata`: `forge/logs/org.springframework:spring-expression:6.2.8/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-21T14-35-37-868367Z.log` fails with `Could not find agent library native-image-agent ... libnative-image-agent.so`. That points to an environment/tooling problem after the javac fix, not to a remaining compile error in the preserved branch.\\n\\nRecommended manual next steps:\\n- Review the preserved branch and confirm the updated `ReflectivePropertyAccessorInnerOptimalPropertyAccessorTest` is the change to keep.\\n- Re-run the failed verification with a GraalVM installation that includes `native-image-agent`, or verify metadata generation manually in an environment where that agent library is available.\\n- If the rerun is clean, open a PR from the preserved branch or cherry-pick the preserved changes onto a fresh fix branch.\"}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
