the string 'N/A'\");\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:256:        public void serialize(DynamicAccessStatsValue value, JsonGenerator generator, SerializerProvider serializers) throws IOException {\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:261:            generator.writeObject(value.dynamicAccessStats());\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:268:        public DynamicAccessStatsValue deserialize(JsonParser parser, DeserializationContext context) throws IOException {\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:275:                JsonNode coverageRatioNode = node.get(\"coverageRatio\");\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:278:                if (coveredCallsNode != null && coverageRatioNode != null && totalCallsNode != null && breakdownNode != null) {\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:279:                    DynamicAccessStats dynamicAccessStats = parser.getCodec().treeToValue(node, DynamicAccessStats.class);\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:280:                    return DynamicAccessStatsValue.available(dynamicAccessStats);\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:283:            throw JsonMappingException.from(parser, \"Dynamic access stats must be an object or the string 'N/A'\");\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:4:service of §GOAL-maximize-library-coverage and\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:34:§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:39:2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:41:3. **Code coverage improvement** — planned workflow that creates new tests for\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:43:   ordinary API and execution coverage beyond dynamic-access call coverage, as\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:44:   defined by §FS-forge-code-coverage-improvement.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:73:### FS-forge-code-coverage-improvement: Code coverage improvement\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:76:code coverage, not only dynamic-access coverage (see\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:77:§WF-code-coverage-improvement), broadening the library coverage outcome\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:78:described in §GOAL-maximize-library-coverage. The workflow creates or improves\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:82:Those tests must live in a separate code coverage test suite, not in the test\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:86:dynamic-access coverage workflow defined in §WF-improve-library-coverage.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:88:coverage asks whether tests exercise calls that require reachability metadata;\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:89:code coverage improvement asks whether tests exercise the broader library API\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:92:metadata-relevant coverage from broader behavior coverage.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:100:| **Forge metrics directory** | The `forge/` subdirectory of the reachability checkout, used as the transient staging area for a run's in-flight metrics (`.pending_metrics.json`) until the PR step reads them. Durable per-library run metrics persist to `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json` (§FS-forge-run-metrics). |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:104:| **Workflow engine** | A registered state-machine-like workflow implementation among the core workflow objects in [ai_workflows/core/](../ai_workflows/core/), such as `basic_iterative` or `dynamic_access_iterative`. The engine owns prompts, command execution, retries, transitions, and terminal status selection for one run. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:109:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:110:| **Dynamic-access exhaust report** | Durable coordinate-scoped JSON state for chunked dynamic-access work. It records the coordinate, issue number, class threshold, processed/exhausted/failed classes, and the latest published chunk PR/commit. It is stored in a stable location derived from the target test suite (for example under `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`) so orchestration scripts can find it from the coordinate alone. It does not predefine all chunks; each resume regenerates the current dynamic-access report and filters out exhausted classes. Specified by §WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:111:| **Chunked dynamic-access workflow** | Dynamic-access generation mode for oversized `library-new-request` and `library-update-request` issues. `forge_metadata.py` owns the class threshold decision and passes the current chunk size to the workflow. The workflow processes at most that many uncovered classes, publishes that chunk, then resumes after the chunk PR merges. PR linking rules are in §WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:113:| **Library update target** | The metadata and test directories selected for a `library-update-request` coordinate (§WF-improve-library-coverage.3). Resolution records the requested coordinate, match type (`tested-version`, `metadata-version`, `default-for`, or `new-version`), matched index entry, resolved metadata version, resolved test version, and edit directories. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:142:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:143:  workflows (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow).\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:170:  If the current dynamic-access report has more uncovered classes than this\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:178:  testing, dynamic-access reporting, native metadata exploration, metadata\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:196:  `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json`, as required by\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:206:  `improve-coverage-…`, `fix-javac-…`, `fix-java-run-…`,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:214:`stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json` so cost, token,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:215:coverage, and status evidence stays attached to the library version it describes\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:216:(§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage). During a run, in-flight metrics are staged\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:335:- Dynamic-access coverage remains missing or suspiciously low after a\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:340:- Publication detects a severe metadata, test, or coverage anomaly that makes\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:345:download failures, GitHub API/status failures, rate limits, runner outages,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:392:noise, GitHub status/API failures, Maven download failures, or other external\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:441:| `RUN_STATUS_CHUNK_READY` | A chunked dynamic-access run reached a reviewable class boundary and §FS-local-ci-equivalent-verification passed for the current part. The current part is PR-eligible, and the issue must not be resumed until the part PR has merged. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:444:The exit code is `0` for PR-eligible statuses and `1` for failure.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:449:must run or refresh the dynamic-access report before choosing the execution\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:450:mode. If the current report has more uncovered dynamic-access classes than the\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:459:`chunked-dynamic-access` label. The normal project status remains the run-state\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:465:by §WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:471:(§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking).\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:483:| `library-new-request` | `add_new_library_support.py` | new library support (§WF-add-new-library-support), which runs dynamic-access generation plus native metadata tracing and verification |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:484:| `library-update-request` | `improve_library_coverage.py`, or the missing-version router | dynamic-access coverage improvement (§WF-improve-library-coverage) |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:488:| code coverage improvement (planned) | — | code coverage improvement (§WF-code-coverage-improvement) |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:492:separate queue: it is the most basic workflow and the fallback the dynamic-access\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:493:workflow delegates to when a library turns out to have no dynamic access\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:503:§GOAL-minimize-generation-cost), token, iteration, LOC, coverage (in service\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:504:of §GOAL-maximize-library-coverage), dynamic-access, and metadata metrics.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:507:starting with fixture-backed E2E coverage for the orchestration boundary; see\nforge/docs/README.md:63:- [workflows/dynamic-access.md](workflows/dynamic-access.md) — `WF-dynamic-access-workflow`.\nforge/docs/README.md:64:- [workflows/improve-library-coverage.md](workflows/improve-library-coverage.md) — `WF-improve-library-coverage`.\nforge/docs/README.md:68:- [workflows/code-coverage-improvement.md](workflows/code-coverage-improvement.md) — `WF-code-coverage-improvement` and `WF-code-coverage-improvement-architecture`: planned code coverage workflow, behavior and architecture in one file.\nforge/docs/README.md:72:code coverage workflow above do.\nstats/org.jline/jline-console/3.22.0/execution-metrics.json:8:    \"strategy_name\": \"javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\",\nstats/org.jline/jline-console/3.22.0/execution-metrics.json:14:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\nstats/org.jline/jline-console/3.22.0/e