cessOutputDir = layout.buildDirectory.dir(\"native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access\")\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:315:    task.setDescription(\"Builds native tests with dynamic-access tracking and reuses Gradle up-to-date checks when inputs and classpath are unchanged\")\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:333:    task.outputs.dir(dynamicAccessOutputDir)\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:334:            .withPropertyName(\"dynamicAccessOutputDir\")\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:367:            throw new GradleException(\"Failed to create native-image output directory: ${nativeImageOutputDirectory.absolutePath}\")\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:392:        throw new GradleException(\"Cannot derive TraceMetadataConditionPackages for ${libraryGAV}: ${userCodeFilterPath} must contain a rules array.\")\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:418:        throw new GradleException(\"Cannot derive TraceMetadataConditionPackages for ${libraryGAV}: ${userCodeFilterPath} has no includeClasses package rules.\")\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:487:        showExceptions = true\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:19:Forge is located inside `graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge`. The parent checkout is the default reachability repository, and successful run metrics are written under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json`. Top-level automation still creates one detached metadata-repo worktree per issue run; the run's pending metrics root is the same worktree's `forge/` directory (§WF-forge-workflow-drivers, §FS-durable-generation-logs).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:80:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5`.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:85:- On success, writes metrics into `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json` (§FS-durable-generation-logs).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:95:- Script results are written in `output/results.json` (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow, §WF-forge-workflow-drivers).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:101:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:126:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:262:- JaCoCo XML coverage parser:\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:386:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:421:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:423:If the library has no dynamic access, the workflow falls back to the standard `basic_iterative` strategy automatically.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:435:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4` | `pi` | Library source code |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:436:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_codex-5.3` | `pi` | Library source code |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:437:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_codex_gpt-5.4` | `codex` | Library source code |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:438:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_codex_codex-5.3` | `codex` | Library source code |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:439:| `dynamic_access_test_sources_codex_gpt-5.4` | `codex` | Upstream test sources |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:440:| `dynamic_access_test_sources_codex_codex-5.3` | `codex` | Upstream test sources |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:441:| `dynamic_access_documentation_sources_codex_gpt-5.4` | `codex` | Documentation artifacts |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:442:| `dynamic_access_documentation_sources_codex_codex-5.3` | `codex` | Documentation artifacts |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:443:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_with_tests_codex_gpt-5.4` | `codex` | Source code + tests |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:444:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_with_tests_codex_codex-5.3` | `codex` | Source code + tests |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:445:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_with_documentation_codex_gpt-5.4` | `codex` | Source code + docs |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:446:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_with_documentation_codex_codex-5.3` | `codex` | Source code + docs |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:447:| `dynamic_access_test_sources_with_documentation_codex_gpt-5.4` | `codex` | Tests + docs |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:448:| `dynamic_access_test_sources_with_documentation_codex_codex-5.3` | `codex` | Tests + docs |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:449:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_with_tests_and_documentation_codex_gpt-5.4` | `codex` | All three |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:450:| `dynamic_access_main_sources_with_tests_and_documentation_codex_codex-5.3` | `codex` | All three |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:452:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:456:| `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.4` | `pi` | `javac_iterative` |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:457:| `optimistic_dynamic_access_iterative_pi_gpt-5.4` | `pi` | `optimistic_dynamic_access` |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:459:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:464:  --strategy-name dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4 \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:475:  --strategy-name dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4 \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:482:see `docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md`.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:502:- Parse JaCoCo XML coverage:\nstats/org.eclipse.jetty.websocket/websocket-api/9.4.40.v20210