ic-access workflow engines:\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:22:| `dynamic_access_iterative` | Per-class dynamic-access generation or refinement. It selects one uncovered class at a time, prompts with that class's remaining call sites, verifies coverage deltas, and commits resolved or partially resolved class progress (§WF-dynamic-access-iterative-strategy). | `dynamic_access_*`, `library_update_pi_gpt-5.5` |\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:23:| `optimistic_dynamic_access` | Bulk dynamic-access generation or refinement. It gives the agent the full dynamic-access report and asks for a broad coverage pass, then verifies tests, regenerates the report, commits the attempt, and runs the native-test verification gate (§WF-dynamic-access-bulk-strategy). | `dynamic_access_bulk_*`, `dynamic_access_graphify_bulk_*`, `library_update_dynamic_access_bulk_pi_gpt-5.5` |\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:24:| `increase_dynamic_access_coverage` | Composite coverage workflow. It optionally runs a configured primary workflow first, then runs the iterative dynamic-access phase against any remaining uncovered call sites (§WF-dynamic-access-composite-strategy). | `optimistic_dynamic_access_iterative_*`, `library_update_optimistic_pi_gpt-5.5`, Java-fix composite strategies |\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:32:#### WF-dynamic-access-iterative-strategy: Iterative dynamic-access strategy\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:34:`dynamic_access_iterative` is the required engine when Forge must make\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:35:class-scoped, reviewable progress through a dynamic-access report. It generates\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:36:the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to the basic iterative workflow\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:39:repair attempts, coverage-delta checks, per-class checkpointing, and native-test\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:40:verification after each configured batch of coverage-gain commits.\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:44:verification gates. Otherwise it returns success only when the dynamic-access\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:47:#### WF-dynamic-access-bulk-strategy: Bulk dynamic-access strategy\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:49:`optimistic_dynamic_access` is the bulk engine. It is used when Forge should\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:50:give the agent the full dynamic-access report and ask for a broad pass rather\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:52:attempt, for library-update coverage improvement, and for Graphify-assisted\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:56:The bulk engine refreshes the dynamic-access report before prompting. If the\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:67:#### WF-dynamic-access-composite-strategy: Composite dynamic-access strategy\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:69:`increase_dynamic_access_coverage` is the composite engine. If the strategy\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:71:primary workflow is returned unchanged and the dynamic-access coverage phase is\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:73:dynamic-access phase, using the same strategy bundle's dynamic-access prompt\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:75:directly with the iterative dynamic-access phase.\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:79:iterative phase refines remaining call sites; and library-update coverage\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:80:strategies, where Forge improves dynamic-access coverage on existing tests\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:83:### WF-dynamic-access-fallback-and-failure: Required fallback and failure behavior\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:87:dynamic-access report cannot provide guidance: the Gradle report task fails,\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:88:the report file is missing or unparsable, dynamic-access reporting is disabled,\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:89:or the report has zero dynamic-access calls. Once a dynamic-a